<h1>Problem 577 - 2009 Balkan MO, P2 of 4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(MN\) be a line parallel to the side \(BC\) of a triangle \(ABC\), with \(M\) on the side \(AB\) and \(N\) on the side \(AC\). The lines \(BN\) and \(CM\) meet at point \(P\). The circumcircles of triangles \(BMP\) and \(CNP\) meet at two distinct points \(P\) and \(Q\). Prove that \(\angle BAQ = \angle CAP\).</p>
